:::summary
The oceans cover more than 70 percent of Earth's surface and contain over 97 percent of all the water on our planet, making them the dominant feature of the world God created. They regulate Earth's climate, support an extraordinary diversity of life, and have shaped the course of human history from the first seafarers to the Age of Exploration and beyond. The Bible speaks of God's mastery over the seas as a sign of His sovereignty, and the oceans remain among the most awe-inspiring expressions of His creative power.
:::

